{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "23", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "36", "S": "38"}}, "news": [{"title": "Andhra Pradesh plans rental housing projects for workers near industrial clusters", "para": "Andhra Pradesh is assessing demand for affordable rental housing for industrial workers, targeting 13 key clusters. This initiative, aligned with the Union government's scheme, aims to provide safe, quality accommodation for migrant workers and those in informal settlements. By addressing housing shortages, the state seeks to boost worker welfare, improve productivity, and attract further industrial investment.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/andhra-pradesh-to-launch-affordable-rental-housing-for-workers-near-industrial-clusters/131925643?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-995550/131925643.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Prepare groundwater policy: Bihar CM", "para": "Bihar Chief Minister Samrat Choudhary has directed officials to swiftly develop a groundwater policy for conservation and sustainable management of the state's water resources. Emphasizing the need for a robust institutional framework and coordinated departmental efforts, he urged acceleration of the proposed Bihar Groundwater Management and Regulation Act, 2026.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/bihar-cm-urges-swift-development-of-groundwater-policy-for-sustainable-management/131925594?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2081422/131925594.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Can\u2019t delay conveyance over future TDR use: Bombay HC", "para": "The Bombay High Court has ruled that housing societies can receive unilateral deemed conveyance of land, even if future development potential on public amenity plots is involved. Justice Sandeep Marne stated that conveyance shouldn't be delayed until the municipal corporation acquires such land. The court modified a previous order, directing conveyance of four acres instead of five, while allowing the builder to claim benefits like TDR for reserved land portions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bombay-high-court-upholds-deemed-conveyance-for-vile-parle-societies/131924883?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-299393/131924883.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}